main event: Circular lights were observed at 50 degrees elevation in flight to the northeast at a very fast speed, appearing as bright as a first magnitude star.
interesting points: The sighting was recorded on May 23, 1964., The object was described as having a very fast speed., The observation was made from an altitude of 7000 feet., The lights were reported at a bearing of 343 degrees., The military source indicated that the lights might be attributable to reflection or natural causes.
sighted object: one circular light in the sky
